{
  "AC": "Recreating test fails before the fix and passes after. doctor (+ store) enforce root == meta.shadir/files; doctor fixups are idempotent, apply across DBs, and announce when they run. SHA path collisions in doctor/ingest use DUP (newer; else smaller SHA). shadup mv a b: end a, end old b if any, insert b with a.sha start=NOW end=NULL (no DUP). Roxy.Music rename can resume afterward.",
  "ActualSummary": "Added shadup doctor to normalize stored_files.root to ${meta.shadir}/files, end-date same-SHA path dupes, DUP different-SHA collisions, and enforce the canonical root on store/reindex. Sampled -v=RATIO action dump (default 0.01) with full (r,d,f) tuples. mv now end-dates any prior occupant of the destination path. Recreating tests cover dual-root failure then doctor recovery.",
  "BaseSha": "f5ed6ecf36cb238db229ecff9121421551c784c7",
