    "raw": "1. Create a recreating test for `shadup mv` failing when matched rows span multiple store roots (album ingested partly under `files/` root and partly with the album dir as root).\n\n2. Then STOP. Explain the failing scenario to the user with simple test values as examples (toy paths/roots), not production paths.\n\n3. User and a high-capability agent discuss the solution. Expect: ingestion updates so new stores stay consistent, plus idempotent data fixups that apply to all DBs. Every such fixup must announce when they run.\n\n4. Acceptance: make the recreating test pass under the agreed fix.\n\n5. Reminder: after this lands, go back to the Roxy.Music* directory rename fixup that was blocked by this bug.\n\n## Agreed direction (partial; not a full redesign)\n\nMisdesign: `stored_files.root` can disagree with the store layout. We are **not** removing `root` yet.\n\nInvariant going forward:\n- `stored_files.root` MUST equal `${meta.shadir}/files`\n  (meta key is `shadir`; path is that value + `/files`).\n\nEnforcement:\n- `shadup doctor` \u2014 detect + **fix** rows that violate the invariant (idempotent; must announce when the fixup runs).\n- store/ingest path \u2014 **enforce** the same invariant on write so new rows never drift.\n\nCollision after normalizing to one root (doctor / ingest fixup):\n- If two different SHAs claim the same `(root, dirpath, filename)`, keep one at the canonical path and apply the **DUP** rename trick to the other (same idea as album `DUP` / `DUP DUP` on dirnames).\n- Which SHA gets DUP: the **newer** one. If no date is available, DUP the **smaller** SHA (lexicographic).\n\n`shadup mv a b` (history, not blob overwrite; no DUP):\n- End-date path `a`: set `end=NOW()` on the active row for `a`.\n- If path `b` already has an active row: set `end=NOW()` on that row too (displace old `b`).\n- Insert a new active row for path `b` with `a`'s SHA: `start=NOW()`, `end=NULL`.\n- Disk follows the same rename into `b`; content-addressed blobs under `data/` are unchanged."
  },
